      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "15 to 30 cm of snow, and even more in some localities, will fall on Tuesday. The wind will be strong to storm force in some cases. The wind will transport the new snow. Further wind slabs will form. <br/> <br/> The snowpack will be prone to triggering over a wide area. The new snow and wind slabs are lying on top of a weakly bonded old snowpack. Distinct weak layers exist in the bottom section of the old snowpack. This applies in particular on west, north and east facing slopes in areas close to the tree line, and above the tree line. <br/> <br/> The rain will give rise as the day progresses to gradual and thorough wetting of the snowpack at low altitude."
      },
      "source": {
        "provider": {
          "name": "LWD K\u00e4rnten",
          "website": "https://lawinenwarndienst.ktn.gv.at/?lang=en"
        }
      },
      "tendency": [
